1
00:00:03,203 --> 00:00:04,571
No wonder you were looking
for Hong the other day.

2
00:00:04,571 --> 00:00:07,107
Everyone on the island knows about it.

3
00:00:07,107 --> 00:00:10,276
But why do you think that kid
has a way to break the wish?

4
00:00:12,245 --> 00:00:16,749
My friend said Hong doesn't seem
like an ordinary person.

5
00:00:17,517 --> 00:00:21,420
Before this, did he say anything to you?

6
00:00:23,256 --> 00:00:25,291
No.

7
00:00:25,291 --> 00:00:29,960
Even if he had said something,
I wouldn't have paid much attention.

8
00:00:29,996 --> 00:00:34,265
You know, in a doctor's eyes,
there are only two types of people.

9
00:00:34,265 --> 00:00:38,071
One is the sick, and the other is the healthy.

10
00:00:38,071 --> 00:00:42,108
So, I don't think
there's anything special about him.

11
00:00:42,108 --> 00:00:43,568
I see.

12
00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,380
But...

13
00:00:47,380 --> 00:00:50,116
Mr. Hua, it's been so many years.

14
00:00:50,116 --> 00:00:52,885
Have you really never thought
of going back to the main island?

15
00:00:54,654 --> 00:00:56,068
Just once.

16
00:00:57,123 --> 00:01:00,593
When my mentor was about to pass away,

17
00:01:00,593 --> 00:01:03,729
I bought a ferry ticket
to rush back and see him.

18
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:07,733
Suddenly, a storm broke out,

19
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:11,270
causing the ferry to be canceled.

20
00:01:11,971 --> 00:01:14,673
After that, whenever I bought a ticket,

21
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:18,411
something unexpected would always happen,

22
00:01:18,411 --> 00:01:20,613
preventing me from returning
to the main island.

23
00:01:21,815 --> 00:01:26,819
So, this must be the consequence
of your wish, Mr. Hua.

24
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:31,590
Even if you want to go back, you can't.

25
00:01:33,493 --> 00:01:35,327
That's fine.

26
00:01:37,931 --> 00:01:42,068
My self-exile is for atonement.

27
00:01:42,068 --> 00:01:45,337
So, life shouldn't be too easy for me.

28
00:01:47,340 --> 00:01:49,742
Not being able to see family and friends

29
00:01:51,244 --> 00:01:53,545
is a burden I should bear.

30
00:01:54,447 --> 00:01:58,184
But Mr. Hua, don't you think
the price is too high?

31
00:01:58,184 --> 00:02:03,353
But to me, a wish is a choice.

32
00:02:03,353 --> 00:02:07,458
Whether it's a gain or a loss
depends on how you look at it.

33
00:02:08,895 --> 00:02:10,729
As for...

34
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:14,033
whether the wish can be broken,

35
00:02:14,667 --> 00:02:16,969
I don't really care that much.

36
00:02:18,037 --> 00:02:19,506
I accept it all.

37
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:21,373
And I'm willing to face it.

38
00:02:28,214 --> 00:02:30,916
So, I'll continue to fight against the wish.

39
00:02:31,951 --> 00:02:33,620
I don't want to give up on myself.

40
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:35,754
I want to get He Xiang Yong back.

41
00:02:36,723 --> 00:02:38,824
This is my way of dealing with it.

42
00:02:45,999 --> 00:02:47,766
Thank you, Mr. Hua.

43
00:02:54,073 --> 00:02:55,477
Mr. Hua...

44
00:02:57,410 --> 00:03:00,046
Although you say it so nonchalantly,

45
00:03:00,046 --> 00:03:03,082
I can feel that you haven't really let it go.

46
00:03:03,082 --> 00:03:05,284
Actually, there's no need to let it go.

47
00:03:06,252 --> 00:03:08,853
Just reconcile with it.
Just embrace it.

48
00:03:11,057 --> 00:03:14,894
Be brave and accept
the broken version of yourself.

49
00:03:14,894 --> 00:03:17,597
Then, you can become a better person.

50
00:03:17,597 --> 00:03:21,400
I truly hope you can go back
to the main island to save people one day.

51
00:03:23,903 --> 00:03:26,538
I can save people while staying here, too.

52
00:03:28,508 --> 00:03:31,176
I also hope you can save yourself, Mr. Hua.

53
00:03:32,312 --> 00:03:35,413
Rescue the version of yourself
who's still stuck in that year.

54
00:04:36,309 --> 00:04:39,045
Mom, I'm home!

55
00:04:39,045 --> 00:04:40,647
Oh, so you still know how to come home?

56
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:42,682
I thought you'd become a main islander.

57
00:04:42,682 --> 00:04:45,783
Don't be like that.
I brought a surprise for you.

58
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,787
I brought it back for you.
The thing you nag about every morning.

59
00:04:49,789 --> 00:04:52,859
Chocola BB Plus from Japan.

60
00:04:52,859 --> 00:04:54,694
Are you looking for a salary advance?

61
00:04:54,694 --> 00:04:57,862
No. Don't you nag about it every morning?

62
00:04:57,864 --> 00:05:00,365
Vitamin B gives you good energy.

63
00:05:01,434 --> 00:05:02,935
That's rare.

64
00:05:02,935 --> 00:05:05,571
You actually restocked it for me.

65
00:05:05,571 --> 00:05:06,739
Of course.

66
00:05:06,739 --> 00:05:09,541
After all, gifting health is trendy now. Better than flowers.

67
00:05:09,542 --> 00:05:12,911
Didn't you say taking this
can supplement nutrients and keep you healthy?

68
00:05:12,912 --> 00:05:16,314
It gives you a healthy glow
and keeps you beautiful forever.

69
00:05:16,349 --> 00:05:18,851
You're such a sweet talker.

70
00:05:19,819 --> 00:05:23,021
Did you win the receipt or the lottery?

71
00:05:24,457 --> 00:05:27,192
Bingo! I won the jackpot.

72
00:05:28,127 --> 00:05:30,664
I checked out a piece of land the other day.

73
00:05:30,664 --> 00:05:33,697
- I think the location of that land...
- Wait, I didn't mean that lottery.

74
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,901
I won the lottery in love.

75
00:05:36,636 --> 00:05:38,704
Can you get to the point?

76
00:05:40,106 --> 00:05:43,609
Yesterday, I confessed to Hama-chan.

77
00:05:45,678 --> 00:05:48,080
You like Hama-chan?

78
00:05:51,117 --> 00:05:52,785
That sounds so familiar.

79
00:05:52,785 --> 00:05:54,786
When did I say that?

80
00:05:56,089 --> 00:05:58,458
How come I didn't know?

81
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:01,961
There's a lot you don't know.

82
00:06:01,961 --> 00:06:05,398
Tell me. What else don't I know?

83
00:06:05,398 --> 00:06:06,532
Nothing.

84
00:06:06,532 --> 00:06:08,201
Anyway, just remember one thing.

85
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:10,402
Hama-chan was the one chasing me.
Hama-chan likes me.

86
00:06:10,403 --> 00:06:12,437
That's why I confessed to him.

87
00:06:23,783 --> 00:06:28,253
So, are you two planning
to have a long-distance relationship?

88
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:30,890
Let me tell you, it's a huge test.

89
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:33,426
You need to be prepared.

90
00:06:33,426 --> 00:06:36,660
What long-distance?
The pier is so close to our house.

91
00:06:36,729 --> 00:06:39,465
No, Zhong came for ice yesterday.

92
00:06:39,465 --> 00:06:43,403
He said Hama-chan wants to see the world.

93
00:06:43,403 --> 00:06:46,505
He's planning to sign with the long-haul fleet.

94
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:59,483
Oh, if he hasn't told you yet,
it means he might still be deciding.

95
00:06:59,483 --> 00:07:03,122
Right? It's fine, it's fine.

96
00:07:03,122 --> 00:07:04,991
It's fine.

97
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:07,892
- Thank you. Thank you.
- All right.

98
00:07:24,777 --> 00:07:28,714
I have a new sailor from Japan.

99
00:07:28,714 --> 00:07:30,016
You speak Japanese?

100
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:31,717
Can you go talk to him for me?

101
00:07:31,717 --> 00:07:34,219
Tell him to be more of a team player.
I'll treat you to sashimi later.

102
00:07:34,219 --> 00:07:35,354
Okay, great.

103
00:07:35,354 --> 00:07:37,556
Is he from Japan?

104
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:43,563
Don't mess with me.

105
00:07:43,563 --> 00:07:46,197
I'm sorry. Newbie.

106
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:54,039
Use this. Be careful.

107
00:07:56,909 --> 00:07:58,911
Don't generalize.

108
00:07:58,911 --> 00:08:01,247
Not every Japanese person likes ramen,

109
00:08:01,247 --> 00:08:03,749
reading comics, and playing video games.

110
00:08:03,749 --> 00:08:05,151
Generalize?

111
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:07,152
You know big words!

112
00:08:08,187 --> 00:08:10,522
I have to tell my mom. Hurry up.

113
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:12,625
- Stop recording.
- Come on, say another one.

114
00:08:12,625 --> 00:08:14,861
One last one.

115
00:08:14,861 --> 00:08:16,662
"Pot calling the kettle black."

116
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:18,397
"You can't judge a book by its cover."

117
00:08:19,198 --> 00:08:21,266
You're really good!

118
00:08:34,146 --> 00:08:36,648
Li Wan Zhe. What are you doing?

119
00:08:36,648 --> 00:08:38,717
Hi.

120
00:08:42,822 --> 00:08:44,390
You said you had something to tell me.

121
00:08:44,390 --> 00:08:46,358
So, you just wanted me to drink with you.

122
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:48,861
Cheers.

123
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:50,463
I don't want to.

124
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:52,798
Stop drinking so much.

125
00:08:55,334 --> 00:08:56,835
What are you doing?

126
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:01,406
What are you doing?

127
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:07,613
Are you crazy? Calm down.

128
00:09:07,613 --> 00:09:09,314
Shut up.

129
00:09:13,819 --> 00:09:16,355
Put me down.

130
00:09:16,355 --> 00:09:18,157
Are you drunk?

131
00:09:18,157 --> 00:09:20,125
Yes, I'm drunk.

132
00:09:31,837 --> 00:09:33,906
Li Wan Zhe.

133
00:09:33,906 --> 00:09:36,041
Are you serious?

134
00:09:37,243 --> 00:09:39,644
I've never been more serious.

135
00:12:33,152 --> 00:12:36,955
Then to you, what is love?

136
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:41,393
Love is a fleeting eternity.

137
00:12:41,393 --> 00:12:44,462
Isn't being together every day
and living life happily enough?

138
00:12:45,865 --> 00:12:47,732
Then what about me?

139
00:12:49,335 --> 00:12:53,072
You are someone I like very, very much.

140
00:12:53,072 --> 00:12:55,074
No matter where I am,

141
00:12:55,074 --> 00:12:57,275
you'll always be in my heart.

142
00:13:01,547 --> 00:13:04,183
If anyone tries to hit on you abroad,

143
00:13:04,183 --> 00:13:05,751
you must tell them
that you already have a master.

144
00:13:05,751 --> 00:13:07,419
Understand?

145
00:13:17,229 --> 00:13:20,198
<i>I want to be in love. Just like fireworks.</i>

146
00:13:20,198 --> 00:13:23,233
- <i>Whoosh!</i>
- <i>Bang!</i>

147
00:13:23,233 --> 00:13:26,138
<i>Could it be that all of this...</i>

148
00:13:26,138 --> 00:13:28,940
<i>was granted by a wish?</i>

149
00:13:31,043 --> 00:13:32,912
I'm tired.

150
00:13:32,912 --> 00:13:34,913
I can give you a massage.

151
00:13:36,415 --> 00:13:38,417
It's okay.

152
00:13:38,417 --> 00:13:40,385
Let's just sleep, okay?

153
00:13:53,132 --> 00:13:55,634
Where am I?

154
00:13:58,537 --> 00:14:00,138
Dad.

155
00:14:00,739 --> 00:14:02,307
Dad.

156
00:14:03,475 --> 00:14:05,043
Dad.

157
00:14:15,487 --> 00:14:17,356
Li Wan Zhe.

158
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:19,024
Li Wan Zhe.

159
00:14:20,993 --> 00:14:23,529
He Xiang Yong.

160
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:25,196
Chen Hao Wei.

161
00:14:26,932 --> 00:14:28,700
Chen Hao Wei.

162
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:33,672
Don't waste your breath.

163
00:14:35,708 --> 00:14:37,843
Hong, you finally showed up.

164
00:14:37,843 --> 00:14:39,644
You can help me, right?

165
00:14:40,379 --> 00:14:42,548
Why do you think I can help you?

166
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:45,084
Since you chose to abandon He Xiang Yong,

167
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:46,552
he won't be coming back.

168
00:14:46,552 --> 00:14:49,488
That is something even I cannot change.

169
00:14:49,488 --> 00:14:50,823
Your wish.

170
00:14:50,823 --> 00:14:52,458
Your choice.

171
00:14:52,458 --> 00:14:56,327
Even if you regret it now,
you have to accept it.

172
00:14:57,296 --> 00:14:58,664
I won't accept it!

173
00:14:58,664 --> 00:15:00,833
Then I'll just cancel the wish, okay?

174
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:02,167
I don't want to be Zhong Xiao You anymore.

175
00:15:02,167 --> 00:15:04,803
Give He Xiang Yong back to me, okay?

176
00:15:04,803 --> 00:15:06,605
Oh, humans.

177
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:10,309
The true value of a wish
is not in what you gain.

178
00:15:10,309 --> 00:15:12,144
It's in how you face it.

179
00:15:12,144 --> 00:15:15,045
- Even if the final outcome is what you call "loss."
- Dad.

180
00:15:15,045 --> 00:15:16,015
Chen Hao Wei.

181
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:17,449
You still have to experience it fully.

182
00:15:17,449 --> 00:15:18,717
Chen Hao Wei.

183
00:15:18,717 --> 00:15:20,552
Otherwise, what a waste it would be.

184
00:15:20,552 --> 00:15:22,187
I beg you. I was wrong.

185
00:15:22,187 --> 00:15:24,223
I was wrong. I'll cancel the wish, okay?

186
00:15:24,223 --> 00:15:25,257
I don't want to be Zhong Xiao You anymore.

187
00:15:25,257 --> 00:15:26,625
Give He Xiang Yong back to me.

188
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:27,626
Dad.

189
00:15:27,626 --> 00:15:28,627
I'm He Xiang Yong.

190
00:15:28,627 --> 00:15:30,095
I'm He Xiang Yong!

191
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:32,097
- Xiang Yong.
- Xiang Yong.

192
00:15:32,097 --> 00:15:33,132
Are you kidding me?

193
00:15:33,132 --> 00:15:34,667
How could I not recognize my own son?

194
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,402
- Xiang Yong.
- It's Xiang Yong!

195
00:15:36,402 --> 00:15:37,569
Xiang Yong, how did you find time to visit?

196
00:15:37,569 --> 00:15:38,871
- It's He Xiang Yong.
- He Xiang Yong.

197
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:40,673
- You don't know him either?
- No, we don't.

198
00:15:40,673 --> 00:15:42,141
The one I can't let go of is He Xiang Yong.

199
00:15:42,141 --> 00:15:44,609
He Xiang Yong? Who's that?

200
00:15:44,609 --> 00:15:46,379
The one I've always loved
is also He Xiang Yong.

201
00:15:46,379 --> 00:15:47,379
He Xiang Yong?

202
00:15:47,379 --> 00:15:50,683
If he were anything like you,
I'd kick him to death.

203
00:15:50,683 --> 00:15:51,684
I'm He Xiang Yong.

204
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:53,018
I'm He Xiang Yong!

205
00:15:53,018 --> 00:15:55,888
Please don't go, okay?

206
00:15:55,888 --> 00:15:57,890
No!

207
00:15:57,890 --> 00:16:00,225
No! I'm He Xiang Yong!

208
00:16:00,225 --> 00:16:02,061
I'm He Xiang Yong.

209
00:16:02,061 --> 00:16:03,395
Chen Hao Wei. I'm He Xiang Yong.

210
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:04,897
Believe me. I'm He Xiang Yong.

211
00:16:04,897 --> 00:16:05,899
Don't leave me, okay?

212
00:16:05,899 --> 00:16:06,931
- Okay.
- I'm He Xiang Yong.

213
00:16:06,931 --> 00:16:07,933
- I believe you.
- Believe me.

214
00:16:07,933 --> 00:16:09,601
- Believe me. I'm really He Xiang Yong.
- I believe you.

215
00:16:09,601 --> 00:16:12,304
- I do. I believe you.
- I really am.

216
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,839
You were having a nightmare.

217
00:16:13,839 --> 00:16:15,207
I dreamt of Hong.

218
00:16:15,207 --> 00:16:16,809
He wanted me to accept the cost of the wish.

219
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,911
To accept that He Xiang Yong no longer exists.

220
00:16:18,911 --> 00:16:20,579
I don't want to. I'm He Xiang Yong.

221
00:16:20,579 --> 00:16:23,914
- I'm He Xiang Yong. Believe me.
- It's okay. It's okay.

222
00:16:23,914 --> 00:16:26,017
It was just a dream. It wasn't real.

223
00:16:26,719 --> 00:16:29,519
No. The dream felt so real.

224
00:16:29,588 --> 00:16:31,256
And things are different now.

225
00:16:31,256 --> 00:16:32,658
If your dream represents
what happened in the past,

226
00:16:32,658 --> 00:16:34,026
what about my dream?

227
00:16:34,026 --> 00:16:35,728
It must be something
that will happen in the future.

228
00:16:35,728 --> 00:16:37,930
No. I don't want He Xiang Yong to disappear.

229
00:16:37,930 --> 00:16:40,399
I-If Hong won't help me, what should I do?

230
00:16:40,399 --> 00:16:42,047
It's okay.

231
00:16:46,805 --> 00:16:49,775
No matter what happens to you,

232
00:16:49,775 --> 00:16:52,277
I'll be by your side.

233
00:16:55,047 --> 00:16:57,782
Just like you said you'd catch me,

234
00:16:58,917 --> 00:17:01,219
I'll catch you, too.

235
00:17:03,489 --> 00:17:05,957
I don't want to disappear.

236
00:17:06,892 --> 00:17:09,427
I don't want to disappear.

237
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:13,998
It's okay. You're safe now.

238
00:17:24,309 --> 00:17:25,645
- Angela!
- Listen.

239
00:17:25,645 --> 00:17:26,645
- We're here.
- When we were kids,

240
00:17:26,645 --> 00:17:29,348
developing a resort on our island

241
00:17:29,348 --> 00:17:31,150
was a very good choice.

242
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:33,385
And our elders have a legend.

243
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,854
If you throw a stone into the sea

244
00:17:35,854 --> 00:17:37,523
to exchange energy with a meteor,

245
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,091
your wish will come true.

246
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:41,427
For a group building a resort,
this is a great selling point.

247
00:17:41,427 --> 00:17:42,761
- Li Wan Zhe, come help.
- Right?

248
00:17:42,761 --> 00:17:45,798
<i>When the meteor shower arrives,</i>

249
00:17:45,798 --> 00:17:48,200
<i>you throw the meteor fragment into the sea.</i>

250
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,402
<i>Bam!</i>

251
00:17:50,402 --> 00:17:51,537
<i>See?</i>

252
00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:56,574
<i>When your wish combines with that energy, it will come true!</i>

253
00:17:56,675 --> 00:17:58,343
This needs to go in the fridge quickly.

254
00:17:58,343 --> 00:17:59,445
Where do you want it?

255
00:17:59,445 --> 00:18:00,846
- Just take it out.
- The stone.

256
00:18:00,846 --> 00:18:01,980
- Li Wan Zhe.
- Bring it here.

257
00:18:01,980 --> 00:18:04,383
- Come here.
- What do you want?

258
00:18:04,383 --> 00:18:05,984
Give me five minutes.

259
00:18:05,984 --> 00:18:07,518
Fine.

260
00:18:10,622 --> 00:18:12,291
Go ahead. Five minutes.

261
00:18:12,291 --> 00:18:14,326
The cave stone.

262
00:18:14,326 --> 00:18:16,929
Someone must have thrown a stone
into the sea when we were wishing.

263
00:18:16,929 --> 00:18:18,964
That's the only way our wishes
could have come true.

264
00:18:18,964 --> 00:18:20,365
So?

265
00:18:20,365 --> 00:18:21,467
So...

266
00:18:21,467 --> 00:18:23,702
So, if we go and get the stone back,

267
00:18:23,702 --> 00:18:25,938
the wish might be canceled.

268
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,706
Are you crazy? The ocean is so vast.

269
00:18:28,706 --> 00:18:30,875
How are you going to find one specific stone?

270
00:18:31,977 --> 00:18:33,912
What do you mean?

271
00:18:33,912 --> 00:18:36,516
Don't you want to solve this anymore?

272
00:18:36,516 --> 00:18:38,649
I'm doing great right now.
I have no problems at all.

273
00:18:38,649 --> 00:18:40,620
You're fine, but I'm not!

274
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:41,620
I...

275
00:18:41,620 --> 00:18:43,754
Right now, no one even knows
who He Xiang Yong is anymore.

276
00:18:43,755 --> 00:18:46,792
If this continues,
I might disappear from this world!

277
00:18:46,792 --> 00:18:48,760
That's not my problem.

278
00:18:51,830 --> 00:18:53,332
Right.

279
00:18:53,332 --> 00:18:56,301
My disappearance really isn't important to you.

280
00:18:56,301 --> 00:18:58,136
But what about Xiao Hai?

281
00:18:58,904 --> 00:19:01,074
Things are only good with him for now.

282
00:19:01,074 --> 00:19:03,907
Once your wish starts to backfire,
it'll be too late for regrets.

283
00:19:05,377 --> 00:19:07,545
Are you trying to scare me?

284
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:11,082
You're scared, aren't you?

285
00:19:12,684 --> 00:19:15,320
You're actually very worried, right?

286
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:21,226
Li Wan Zhe, I know you too well.

287
00:19:21,226 --> 00:19:24,362
We grew up together like brothers.

288
00:19:25,097 --> 00:19:28,267
You've always been a coward.

289
00:19:28,267 --> 00:19:30,568
You only know how to run away.

290
00:19:31,436 --> 00:19:33,906
That's why you're terrified.

291
00:19:33,906 --> 00:19:36,175
You're afraid if I find that stone,

292
00:19:36,175 --> 00:19:38,476
Xiao Hai won't love you anymore, right?

293
00:19:41,647 --> 00:19:44,016
Anyway, I've told you about Xiao Hai.

294
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:48,618
If you keep running away,
it might end up like your wish.

295
00:19:48,618 --> 00:19:52,422
Just like fireworks,
once they burn out, they're gone.

296
00:19:52,424 --> 00:19:54,158
That's it.

297
00:19:56,795 --> 00:19:58,864
You say I'm your brother?

298
00:19:58,864 --> 00:20:01,265
Would a true friend be so selfish?

299
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:05,835
I won't let you do anything
to ruin my relationship with Xiao Hai.

300
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:08,674
You keep talking about
how you're going to disappear.

301
00:20:08,674 --> 00:20:11,777
Have you ever thought maybe
you don't even deserve to exist in this world?

302
00:20:11,777 --> 00:20:13,745
What did you say?

303
00:20:13,745 --> 00:20:16,147
- I'm sorry.
- Screw you!

304
00:20:19,685 --> 00:20:20,718
Li Wan Zhe!

305
00:20:20,718 --> 00:20:22,487
Are you crazy?

306
00:20:27,025 --> 00:20:28,926
Li Wan Zhe!

307
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:33,198
What the hell do you want?

308
00:20:33,198 --> 00:20:34,466
Say it!

309
00:20:34,466 --> 00:20:36,068
What's your problem?

310
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,402
- Get up and fight!
- Stop it!

311
00:20:37,402 --> 00:20:39,504
What's going on? Why are they fighting?

312
00:20:39,504 --> 00:20:40,505
Stop fighting!

313
00:20:40,505 --> 00:20:42,174
- Come on!
- Aren't we supposed to be moving stuff?

314
00:20:42,174 --> 00:20:43,175
- Didn't you want to fight?
- Why are you fighting?

315
00:20:43,175 --> 00:20:44,376
Come here!

316
00:20:44,376 --> 00:20:45,944
Don't do this!

317
00:20:45,944 --> 00:20:47,179
Stop it!

318
00:20:47,179 --> 00:20:49,381
You guys!

319
00:20:49,381 --> 00:20:51,516
That's enough!

320
00:20:51,516 --> 00:20:54,385
- No fighting!
- Calm down!

321
00:20:55,187 --> 00:20:57,022
Why are you fighting?

322
00:20:57,022 --> 00:20:58,957
Why did you hit Wan Zhe?

323
00:20:58,957 --> 00:21:00,525
Oh, for goodness' sake.

324
00:21:02,794 --> 00:21:04,463
Oh dear.

325
00:21:04,463 --> 00:21:06,864
It's all broken.

326
00:21:34,893 --> 00:21:36,594
Are you okay?

327
00:21:44,236 --> 00:21:46,805
It's a good thing Mr. He isn't here.

328
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:48,974
If he knew you got into a fight,

329
00:21:48,974 --> 00:21:50,975
he'd definitely scold you.

330
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:55,380
Then let him scold me.

331
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:57,482
He might as well scold me to death.

332
00:21:58,684 --> 00:22:00,652
What on earth am I doing?

333
00:22:00,652 --> 00:22:03,121
Why was I so impulsive?

334
00:22:05,791 --> 00:22:08,426
You were a bit too impulsive just now.

335
00:22:09,194 --> 00:22:12,664
Anyway, the one who throws
the first punch is in the wrong.

336
00:22:12,664 --> 00:22:15,167
That's not the point.

337
00:22:15,167 --> 00:22:17,102
He's Li Wan Zhe.

338
00:22:17,102 --> 00:22:20,003
We've known each other for over 20 years.
This is our first fight ever.

339
00:22:20,038 --> 00:22:22,507
And I was the one who started it.

340
00:22:23,442 --> 00:22:25,910
He'll never forgive me.

341
00:22:35,821 --> 00:22:38,189
Actually, I don't agree with you
looking for that stone.

342
00:22:43,695 --> 00:22:46,365
The sea is so vast, and the stone is so small.

343
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:48,299
How could you possibly find it?

344
00:22:49,334 --> 00:22:52,037
Finding that stone is my only hope now.

345
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:56,171
I haven't even started looking yet.
Why are you shooting me down too?

346
00:22:56,171 --> 00:22:57,942
No.

347
00:23:01,446 --> 00:23:03,981
I just want you to be okay.

348
00:23:05,617 --> 00:23:08,719
I can only be okay if I find He Xiang Yong.

349
00:23:14,860 --> 00:23:16,762
Forget it.

350
00:23:16,762 --> 00:23:18,930
You wouldn't understand right now.

351
00:23:54,900 --> 00:23:57,335
Finding that stone is my only hope now.

352
00:23:57,335 --> 00:24:00,504
I can only be okay if I find He Xiang Yong.

353
00:24:36,908 --> 00:24:39,044
<i>Just let me...</i>

354
00:24:39,044 --> 00:24:41,612
<i>help you find He Xiang Yong.</i>

355
00:27:01,004 --> 00:27:08,918
[Epilogue]

356
00:27:43,395 --> 00:27:46,698
Why point out the obvious?

357
00:27:46,698 --> 00:27:50,468
Making a wish is a trial of choice.

358
00:27:50,468 --> 00:27:54,105
Every choice, its beginning and its end,

359
00:27:54,105 --> 00:27:58,774
has its own meaning and a reason for existing.

360
00:28:03,181 --> 00:28:05,583
I don't want to just stand by and watch.

361
00:28:07,152 --> 00:28:09,587
This isn't your story.

362
00:28:10,388 --> 00:28:13,425
You and I are both just bystanders.

363
00:28:13,425 --> 00:28:16,926
We have no right to interfere or change these choices.

364
00:29:09,214 --> 00:29:11,716
You must bear the consequences of your wish,
whether they're good or bad.

365
00:29:11,716 --> 00:29:15,418
When a wish comes true,
this is the path you must walk alone.

366
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:18,523
Your own subconscious
led your life to this point.

367
00:29:18,523 --> 00:29:20,158
Now you're blaming it on fate?

368
00:29:20,158 --> 00:29:21,926
Who was the one who started all this?

369
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:23,361
Who was the one dissatisfied with the wish,

370
00:29:23,361 --> 00:29:26,330
and is now delusional enough
to want to change it?

